hopobject.body: Some First Class stamps imipramine in nocturnal enuresis treatment Turkish anti-goverment protesters chant slogans at the entrance of Gezi park during a protest after their first day of fasting for the Muslim holy month of Ramadan on Istiklal street, the main shopping corridor, on July 9, 2013 in Istanbul. During the month devout Muslims must abstain from food, drink and sex from dawn until sunset, when they break the fast with the meal known as Iftar.
